Class SimpleProduct

  • java.lang.Object
    • domain.product.Product
      • domain.product.SimpleProduct
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDeepCopy, IProduct, IShoppingCartElement
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExtendedProduct

    public class SimpleProduct
extends Product
    Implementation of a product that only consists of a single item with a name and price. It extends the abstract Product class.

        public SimpleProduct deepCopy()
        Description copied from interface: IDeepCopy
        Creates and returns a copy of this object. The precise meaning of "copy" may depend on the class of the object. The general intent is that, for any object x, the expression: 
         x.deepCopy() != x
        will be true, and that the expression: 
         x.deepCopy().getClass() == x.getClass()
        will be true, but these are not absolute requirements. While it is typically the case that: 
         x.deepCopy().equals(x)
        will be true, this is not an absolute requirement.
